Let \( f(n) \) be a function defined for \( n \ge 2 \) and \( n \in \mathbb{N} \) which follows the recurrence relation for \( n \ge 3 \):
\[
f(n) = f(n-1) + \frac{4 \cdot (-1)^{(n-1)} \cdot \left(\sum_{d \vert (n-1)} \chi(d)\right)}{n-1}
\]
where \( d \vert (n-1) \) means \( d \) divides \( n-1 \). Assume \( f(2) = -4 \). The function \( \chi(d) \) is defined as:
\[
\chi(d) = \begin{cases} 
1, & \text{if } d = 4k+1 \text{ where } k \text{ is a whole number} \\
-1, & \text{if } d = 4k+3 \text{ where } k \text{ is a whole number} \\
0, & \text{if } d \text{ is an even natural number} 
\end{cases}
\]
Find \( \lim_{n \to \infty} f(n) \).

